===Etymology===
Sanskrit [[avatarah]] "descent (of a [[deity]] from [[heaven]] in [[incarnate]] form)", from [[ava-]] "down" and [[tariti]] "(he) crosses".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The physical [[embodiment]] of an [[idea]] or [[concept]].
# (computing) A [[digital]] [[representation]] of a [[person]] or [[being]].
# ([[Hinduism]]) The earthly [[incarnation]] of a deity, particularly [[Vishnu]].

